post_text:
Today, my students and I start our alphabet countdown to the last day of school. Each day, we will pop open a balloon on our Zoom calls and discover our theme!

I have a lot of fun ideas and most of them don't involve being present in my virtual classroom! Let me know if you would like to join our activities, and I'll share my calendar with you! Activities range from dressing up like an animal (today) to exercising to helping others!

It's also a great opportunity to reinforce those letter/sound concepts with your kids. I'm more than happy to share my calendar so just ask (and share your pictures!).
text:
Today, my students and I start our alphabet countdown to the last day of school. Each day, we will pop open a balloon on our Zoom calls and discover our theme!

I have a lot of fun ideas and most of them don't involve being present in my virtual classroom! Let me know if you would like to join our activities, and I'll share my calendar with you! Activities range from dressing up like an animal (today) to exercising to helping others!

It's also a great opportunity to reinforce those letter/sound concepts with your kids. I'm more than happy to share my calendar so just ask (and share your pictures!).

post_text: In preparation for next school year, Multicultural Academy students will celebrate Moving Up Day today. At the end of the day, students will "move up" to their grade level teacher for next year. (ie - Preschool visits kindergarten; kindergarten visits 1st grade, etc...) Teachers will talk to students about all of the exciting things they will do/learn in the fall. Ask your student what they found out!

post_text: Multicultural Academy middle school students had a special visit today from Shawn Blanchard-author, speaker, and mentorship specialist. He spoke of his journey from the mean streets of Detroit to where he is today. He left students with a message of taking opportunities from obstacles and applying an image of excellence. Students that asked questions were given a copy of his book "How 'Bout That for a Crack Baby".

post_text:
Did you know that April is National Arab American Heritage Month?

This month celebrates the 1,697,570 Arab Americans in the United States. They are Americans of Arab ethnic, cultural and linguistic heritage or identity.
